{
  "text": "B. REFORM AT ALPERT MEDICAL SCHOOL OF BROWN UNIVERSITY Curricular reform around questions of race and racism began at Brown in 2012, when three first-year medical students requested time in the formal medical curriculum to introduce topics related to racial disparities in disease. [CITATION_1] Building on a student-led elective titled \"Healthcare for the Underserved,\"",
